[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       2[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       3[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > **Heads up:** This is a deliberately simplified, illustrative implementation of the pseudocode walkthrough from Recipe 9.9. Real surgical video analysis involves multi-day GPU training runs, transformer architectures processing thousands of frames, and months of expert annotation. This example demonstrates the *shape* of the pipeline using synthetic data and simulated model outputs. It shows how you'd orchestrate the AWS pieces (S3, MediaConvert, SageMaker, DynamoDB, OpenSearch) with boto3. Think of it as a map of the territory, not the territory itself. A starting point, not a destination.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       4[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       5[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       6[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       7[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Setup
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       8[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       9[0m:[38;5;10m[49m You'll need the AWS SDK for Python and a few numerical libraries:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      10[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      11[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```bash
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      12[0m:[38;5;10m[49m pip install boto3 numpy
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      13[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      14[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      15[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Your environment needs credentials configured (via environment variables, an instance profile, or `~/.aws/credentials`). The IAM role or user needs:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      16[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      17[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `s3:GetObject`, `s3:PutObject` (video and frame storage)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      18[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `mediaconvert:CreateJob`, `mediaconvert:GetJob` (frame extraction)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      19[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `sagemaker:CreateTransformJob`, `sagemaker:DescribeTransformJob` (model inference)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      20[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `dynamodb:PutItem`, `dynamodb:UpdateItem`, `dynamodb:Query` (procedure index)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      21[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `es:ESHttpPost`, `es:ESHttpGet` (OpenSearch indexing and search)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      22[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `states:StartExecution` (pipeline orchestration)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      23[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      24[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      25[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      26[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Config and Constants
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      27[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      28[0m:[38;5;10m[49m These go at the top of your module. They define the frame sampling parameters, model configuration, phase definitions, and AWS resource names. In production, most of these would come from environment variables or SSM Parameter Store.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      29[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      30[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      31[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Frame sampling configuration.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      32[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # 1 fps is standard for phase recognition. Phase transitions happen over seconds,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      33[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # not milliseconds, so higher rates just burn GPU time without improving accuracy.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      34[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # For instrument detection, you'd bump this to 5 fps.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      35[0m:[38;5;10m[49m SAMPLE_RATE_FPS = 1
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      36[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      37[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Model input resolution.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      38[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Most surgical video models expect 224x224 or 384x384.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      39[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Higher resolution captures more detail but costs more GPU memory per frame.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      40[0m:[38;5;10m[49m MODEL_INPUT_SIZE = (224, 224)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      41[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      42[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Feature extraction output dimension.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      43[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # ResNet-50 backbone produces 2048-dimensional feature vectors.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      44[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # These get fed into the temporal model.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      45[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FEATURE_DIM = 2048
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      46[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      47[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Batch size for GPU inference.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      48[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # How many frames to process in one forward pass.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      49[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Depends on GPU memory; 32 is safe for most g5 instances.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      50[0m:[38;5;10m[49m BATCH_SIZE = 32
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      51[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      52[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Phase definitions for laparoscopic cholecystectomy.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      53[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # These are the surgical phases the temporal model predicts.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      54[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Other procedure types would have different phase sets.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      55[0m:[38;5;10m[49m CHOLECYSTECTOMY_PHASES = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      56[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "port_placement",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      57[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "initial_dissection",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      58[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "calot_triangle_dissection",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      59[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "clipping_and_cutting",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      60[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "gallbladder_separation",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      61[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "extraction_and_inspection",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      62[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      63[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      64[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Instrument classes the model can detect.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      65[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Multi-label: multiple instruments can be present simultaneously.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      66[0m:[38;5;10m[49m INSTRUMENT_CLASSES = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      67[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "grasper",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      68[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "hook_cautery",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      69[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "scissors",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      70[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "clip_applier",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      71[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "irrigator",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      72[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "specimen_bag",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      73[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      74[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      75[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Event types the model flags.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      76[0m:[38;5;10m[49m EVENT_TYPES = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      77[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "bleeding_minor",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      78[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "bleeding_major",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      79[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "clip_placement",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      80[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "specimen_extraction",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      81[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "conversion_to_open",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      82[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      83[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      84[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Post-processing parameters.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      85[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Minimum phase duration in seconds. No surgical phase lasts less than 30 seconds.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      86[0m:[38;5;10m[49m MIN_PHASE_DURATION_SEC = 30
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      87[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Median filter window for phase smoothing (in frames at SAMPLE_RATE_FPS).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      88[0m:[38;5;10m[49m PHASE_SMOOTH_WINDOW = 15
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      89[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Gap fill for instrument detection: brief disappearances shorter than this
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      90[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # are likely occlusion, not actual instrument removal.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      91[0m:[38;5;10m[49m INSTRUMENT_GAP_FILL_SEC = 3
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      92[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      93[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Confidence thresholds.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      94[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Below these, predictions are marked low-confidence in the output.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      95[0m:[38;5;10m[49m PHASE_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD = 0.70
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      96[0m:[38;5;10m[49m EVENT_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD = 0.50
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      97[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      98[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # AWS resource names. In production, pull these from environment variables.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      99[0m:[38;5;10m[49m RAW_VIDEO_BUCKET = "surgical-video-raw"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     100[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FRAMES_BUCKET = "surgical-frames"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     101[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FEATURES_BUCKET = "surgical-features"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     102[0m:[38;5;10m[49m PROCEDURE_INDEX_TABLE = "procedure-index"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     103[0m:[38;5;10m[49m PROCEDURE_REGISTRY_TABLE = "procedure-registry"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     104[0m:[38;5;10m[49m OPENSEARCH_DOMAIN = "https://vpc-surgical-search-xxxxx.us-east-1.es.amazonaws.com"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     105[0m:[38;5;10m[49m SAGEMAKER_FEATURE_MODEL = "surgical-feature-extractor"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     106[0m:[38;5;10m[49m SAGEMAKER_TEMPORAL_MODEL = "surgical-temporal-model"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     107[0m:[38;5;10m[49m MEDIACONVERT_ROLE_ARN = "arn:aws:iam::123456789012:role/MediaConvertRole"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     108[0m:[38;5;10m[49m MEDIACONVERT_QUEUE_ARN = "arn:aws:mediaconvert:us-east-1:123456789012:queues/Default"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     109[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     110[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     111[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     112[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     113[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 1: Video Ingestion and Metadata Registration
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     114[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     115[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *Maps to pseudocode Step 1: `ingest_video(video_file, metadata)`. When a surgical video arrives from the OR recording system, this function uploads it to encrypted S3 storage, registers it in the procedure tracking table, and returns the procedure ID that links everything together downstream.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     116[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     117[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     118[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import json
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     119[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import uuid
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     120[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import logging
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     121[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import datetime
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     122[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from datetime import timezone
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     123[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from decimal import Decimal
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     124[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     125[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import boto3
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     126[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import numpy as np
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     127[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from botocore.config import Config
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     128[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     129[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Structured logging. In production, use JSON-formatted output for
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     130[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # CloudWatch Logs Insights queries.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     131[0m:[38;5;10m[49m logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     132[0m:[38;5;10m[49m logger.setLevel(logging.INFO)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     133[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     134[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Retry configuration. Surgical video processing involves long-running jobs
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     135[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # and large file transfers. Adaptive retry handles throttling gracefully.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     136[0m:[38;5;10m[49m BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG = Config(retries={"max_attempts": 5, "mode": "adaptive"})
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     137[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     138[0m:[38;5;10m[49m s3_client = boto3.client("s3", config=BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     139[0m:[38;5;10m[49m dynamodb = boto3.resource("dynamodb", config=BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     140[0m:[38;5;10m[49m mediaconvert_client = boto3.client("mediaconvert", config=BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     141[0m:[38;5;10m[49m stepfunctions_client = boto3.client("stepfunctions", config=BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     142[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     143[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     144[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def ingest_video(video_s3_key: str, metadata: dict) -> str:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     145[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     146[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Register a surgical video that has landed in S3 and trigger the analysis pipeline.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     147[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     148[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     In practice, the video is uploaded by the OR recording system (or a transfer
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     149[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     agent) before this function runs. This function handles the metadata registration
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     150[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     and pipeline trigger, not the upload itself.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     151[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     152[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
